        "excerpt":"The Anatomy of an HTML element      The main parts of our element are:      The opening tag:Â This consists of the name of the element (in this case, p), wrapped in opening and closingÂ angle brackets. This states where the element begins or starts to take effect â€” in this case where the start of the paragraph is.   The closing tag:Â This is the same as the opening tag, except that it includes a forward slash before the element name. This states where the element ends â€” in this case where the end of the paragraph is. Failing to include a closing tag is a common beginner error and can lead to strange results.   The content:Â This is the content of the element, which in this case is just text.   The element:Â The opening tagÂ plus the closing tag plus the content equals the element.  ","categories": ["HTML"],
